---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const video = {
  title: 'Meniscus Allograft Transplant Preparation',
  vimeoId: '663169019',
  category: 'Knee Procedures',
  duration: '3:45',
  surgeon: 'Kevin R. Stone, MD',
  year: '2014',
  location: 'San Francisco, CA'
};
---

<Layout title={video.title}>
  <section class="bg-stone-900 text-white py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <a href="/techniques" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-stone-400 hover:text-white text-sm mb-6 transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
        Back to Surgical Techniques
      </a>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400 text-sm font-medium rounded-full">{video.category}</span>
        <span class="text-stone-500">•</span>
        <span class="text-stone-400 text-sm">{video.duration}</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-sm md:text-display-md text-white mb-4">{video.title}</h1>
      <p class="text-stone-400">Performed by {video.surgeon} · {video.year} · {video.location}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-800 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="aspect-video relative rounded-sm overflow-hidden bg-stone-900">
        <iframe src={`https://player.vimeo.com/video/${video.vimeoId}?h=0&title=0&byline=0&portrait=0`} class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <div class="sticky top-24">
            <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-stone-900 mb-4">Quick Facts</h3>
            <dl class="space-y-4 text-sm">
              <div><dt class="text-stone-500">Topic</dt><dd class="font-medium text-stone-900">Graft Preparation</dd></div>
              <div><dt class="text-stone-500">Focus</dt><dd class="font-medium text-stone-900">Sizing & Tissue Handling</dd></div>
              <div><dt class="text-stone-500">Audience</dt><dd class="font-medium text-stone-900">Surgeons & Tissue Banks</dd></div>
            </dl>
            <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-stone-200">
              <a href="/research/meniscus" class="text-sm text-emerald-600 hover:text-emerald-700 flex items-center gap-1">
                View Sizing Research
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-stone-900 mb-6">Summary</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none mb-12">
            <p>Proper preparation of the meniscus allograft is critical to successful transplantation. This video covers tissue bank recommendations for graft sizing and surgical back-table preparation techniques.</p>
            <h3>Key Principles</h3>
            <p>Research has shown that height, weight, and gender correlate with meniscal dimensions, providing tissue banks and surgeons with simple, cost-effective variables for predicting appropriate graft size. The graft must be properly sized, bone plugs shaped, and sutures placed before implantation.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-stone-900 mb-6">Transcript</h2>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-sm p-6 md:p-8">
            <div class="prose prose-stone prose-sm max-w-none">
              <p>This video demonstrates the preparation of meniscus allograft tissue for transplantation. The graft arrives from the tissue bank with bone blocks attached to the anterior and posterior horns.</p>
              <p>The bone blocks are shaped to fit through the prepared tunnels—typically 8-10mm in diameter. Sutures are placed through the bone plugs and the body of the meniscus to allow passage through the tunnels and peripheral fixation.</p>
              <p>Proper sizing is essential: an undersized graft will not adequately distribute load, while an oversized graft may extrude. Patient height, weight, and gender provide reliable sizing parameters.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-100 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
        <a href="/techniques/revision-meniscus" class="text-stone-600 hover:text-stone-900 inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
          Revision Meniscus
        </a>
        <a href="/techniques/knee-dislocation" class="text-emerald-600 hover:text-emerald-700 inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          Next: Knee Dislocation
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
